Statements made as to sentencing.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS, same terms and conditions as probation to apply.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:  
*Serve 120 DAYS in the House of Correction with huber release for work and school (REPORT DATE: 11/3/15); 
*AODA assessment; 
*Maintain absolute sobriety;
*Complete 25 hours of community service;
*Maintain fulltime employment or school; 
*No contact with Johnathan Williams;
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, Court orders amounts to be paid during the term of probation. Any unpaid amount to be converted to a civil judgment.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

